Ladbrokes suspend betting on Alan Pardew to get the sack
The 52 year-old was given his marching orders by referee Kevin Friend after clashing heads with Hull midfielder David Meyler after the Irish international collided with him on the sideline.
Meyler was booked while Pardew was given a red card, to add to a number of previous indiscretions, including clashing with Man City manager Manuel Pellegrini earlier this season.
Following the incident Ladbrokes announced it has suspended betting on the next Premier League manager to lose his job.The company's Alex Donohue said: "We wait to see how Pardew's actions are dealt with.